(10676, 'Sentimientos asociados a la vivencia del desplazamiento (Colombia)', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;es&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumen&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;El art&iacute;culo presenta algunos de los resultados de la Investigaci&oacute;n &nbsp;&ldquo;Significados del de acompa&ntilde;amiento psicosocial &lsquo;Resignificar la experiencia&rsquo; &rdquo; particularmente los relativos a los sentimientos vivenciados por las personas en situaci&oacute;n de desplazamiento beneficiarias de la Fundaci&oacute;n Mencoldes y acompa&ntilde;adas por este proyecto de la Facultad de Psicolog&iacute;a de la Pontificia Universidad Javeriana.&lt;br /&gt; &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;El miedo, la verg&uuml;enza, la tristeza, la incertidumbre, la desconfianza, la a&ntilde;oranza, el sufrimiento, as&iacute; como sus posibilidades de resignificaci&oacute;n se discuten a la luz, de los presupuestos te&oacute;ricos de Agnes Heller, Carlos Castilla del Pino, Pablo Fern&aacute;ndez, Elizabeth Lira, Ignacio Mart&iacute;n Bar&oacute;, Carlos Mart&iacute;n Beristain, entre otros.&lt;br /&gt; &nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;A la vez se presenta el an&aacute;lisis de las narraciones de las personas participantes donde relatan sus sentires durante el desplazamiento forzado y a lo largo del acompa&ntilde;amiento psicosocial. Se hace visible la forma como las personas desplazadas emergen de la tragedia para continuar la vida en contextos desconocidos.&lt;br /&gt; &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;Finalmente se discuten los alcances del proceso de &nbsp;acompa&ntilde;amiento &lsquo;Resignificar la experiencia&rsquo; tanto en sus potencialidades como en sus limites propios y contextuales.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;This article presents some results of our investigation called &lt;em&gt;Feelings associated with the experience of displacement: Giving new meaning to the experience&lt;/em&gt;. Specifically it examines the feelings of people who have been forcibly displaced from their homes; and who have been benefited from the material support of Mencoldes Fundati&oacute;n and were accompanied as part of a project by the Department of psychology of Javeriana University. &lt;br /&gt; &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;Fear, shame, sadness, uncertainty, mistrust, nostalgia, and suffering are analyzed in the light of the theories of Agnes Heller, Carlos Castilla del Pino, Pablo Fern&aacute;ndez, Elizabeth Lira, Ignacio Mart&iacute;n Bar&oacute;, Carlos Mart&iacute;n Beristain, among others. &nbsp;These emotions also are discussed in terms of the possibility of assigning them new meanings. At the same time, the narrations of the participants are looked at from the stand point of the limits of psychological accompaniment. Finally, it is possible to see in what ways the narrators were able to continue their lives in unknown circumstances. &lt;br /&gt; &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;Finally, the limits of psychological accompaniment are discussed as well as its achievements. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
