(10899, 'La préférence pour les jugements rationnels', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;L&rsquo;objet de la pr&eacute;sente communication est d&rsquo;&eacute;tablir l&rsquo;existence d&rsquo;une valorisation des jugements traduisant une rationalit&eacute; chez les individus. Pour ce faire, nous avons &eacute;labor&eacute; un questionnaire permettant de mesurer une pr&eacute;f&eacute;rence pour les jugements rationnels, puis nous avons mis en &oelig;uvre les paradigmes des juges et d&rsquo;auto-pr&eacute;sentation aupr&egrave;s d&rsquo;&eacute;tudiants fran&ccedil;ais. Les r&eacute;sultats confirment nos attentes et permettent d&rsquo;&eacute;tablir qu&rsquo;il existe bien une pr&eacute;f&eacute;rence pour les jugements rationnels, fondant une norme sociale de jugement.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(10900, 'El muro levantado por Israel: los riesgos del antisemitismo', 'titre_article', 6, ';'),
(10901, 'Aspects d’une épistémologie skinnérienne', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt; Apr&egrave;s une pr&eacute;sentation des options skinn&eacute;riennes vis-&agrave;-vis de la science en g&eacute;n&eacute;ral, deux aspects particuliers sont consid&eacute;r&eacute;s&nbsp;: la causalit&eacute; d&rsquo;une part, l&rsquo;explication et les th&eacute;ories scientifiques d&rsquo;autre part. Dans la lign&eacute;e de travaux r&eacute;cents, une mise en perspective des positions de Skinner donne lieu &agrave; deux conclusions provisoires&nbsp;: premi&egrave;rement, l&rsquo;arri&egrave;re-plan th&eacute;orique de ses analyses se r&eacute;sume clairement &agrave; quelques th&eacute;oriciens anglo-saxons de la science moderne&nbsp;; deuxi&egrave;mement, ses conceptions de la causalit&eacute; et de l&rsquo;explication sont loin d&rsquo;&ecirc;tre distinctes et distinguables. Cet article, concernant l&lsquo;opportunit&eacute; d&rsquo;accorder ou non le statut d&rsquo;&eacute;pist&eacute;mologie originale au b&eacute;haviorisme radical skinn&eacute;rien, aboutit donc sur une position mitig&eacute;e, mais propose l&rsquo;&eacute;tayage &eacute;ventuel de cette th&egrave;se par des recherches subs&eacute;quentes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Some skinnerian options about science are first presented&nbsp;: &nbsp;pragmatism in science and the study of the scientists behavior&nbsp;; the technical aspects of science, with respect to the control and prediction of behavior&nbsp;; the formulation and function of scientific laws. Then, among these topics, two basic lines are shown of interest: Skinner&rsquo;s view of causality, and his conceptions about explanation and scientific theories. Some recent studies (Chiesa, 1994; Ringen, 1999; Smith, 1986) have examined these two aspects of skinnerian radical behaviorism. The present work review their arguments, in each case, before concluding on two remarks: firstly, considering the two last centuries, theoritical background of the skinnerian analysis clearly amounts to a few Anglo-Saxons theoricians of modern science; secondly, his conceptions of causality and explanation are far from being distinct and accurate. For instance, skinnerian determinism is not a mecanistic one; behavior is often globally considered, but operant mecanism seems also to operate at a molecular level; a temporal gap remains between behavior and consequence, not always explicitly justified; the equivalence between description and explanation might be discussed; and the reject of certain forms of theories is not uniquely logical. All these points can lead to different philosophical positions. The lack of originality or inaccuracy of some skinnerian options implies to pursue further investigations, in order to defend the building of a proper skinnerian radical behaviorist epistemology. We propose to support this temporary conclusion by future research. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
