(10957, 'La position des sociologues dans le processus de développement :Approche systémique et approche participative.', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;La position des sociologues dans le paysage du processus du d&eacute;veloppement est toujours d&eacute;pendante d&rsquo;une multitude de variables complexes, o&ugrave; se croise le politique et l&rsquo;&eacute;conomique, les strat&eacute;gies individuelle et les strat&eacute;gies institutionnelles. La place des sociologues experts avait beaucoup chang&eacute;e au fil du temps et sous l&rsquo;effet d&rsquo;un nombre d&rsquo;intervenants. Nous assistons, &agrave; la phase actuelle, &agrave; un autre r&ocirc;le du sociologue praticien qui se dessine &agrave; l&rsquo;aide ou sous l&rsquo;influence des bailleurs de fonds.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The position of the sociologists in the landscape of the process of development is always dependent on a multitude of complex variables, or cross the political and economic, individual strategies and institutional strategies.&lt;br /&gt;The place of the expert sociologists had changed a lot in the course of time and under the influence of a number of interferers. In the actual stage, another role of the sociologist practitioner, who takes shape in help or under the influence of the backers, took place.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(10958, 'La médiation sociale : un champ professionnel toujours en quête d’identité', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;La m&eacute;diation est un mode de r&eacute;solution de conflits en plein essor, qui propose &agrave; la soci&eacute;t&eacute; un remaniement de ses fa&ccedil;ons de penser, de dire et d&rsquo;agir h&eacute;rit&eacute;es des ann&eacute;es de crise &eacute;conomique et sociale (1980/90). Elle s&rsquo;est install&eacute;e peu &agrave; peu dans un champ social assez vaste (scolaire, familial&hellip;). La m&eacute;diation, en g&eacute;n&eacute;ral, et plus particuli&egrave;rement celle dite &laquo;&nbsp;sociale&nbsp;&raquo;, qui a &eacute;t&eacute;, d&eacute;velopp&eacute;e en France durant plusieurs ann&eacute;es de la mesure &laquo;&nbsp;emploi jeune&nbsp;&raquo;, souffre d&rsquo;un manque de rep&egrave;res dans sa d&eacute;marche de professionnalisation. En esquissant les limites et les faiblesses du processus de professionnalisation, cet article vise &agrave; d&eacute;montrer l&rsquo;int&eacute;r&ecirc;t de s&rsquo;appuyer sur un r&eacute;f&eacute;rentiel de comp&eacute;tences qui contribuera &agrave; dissiper le flou qui gravite autour des m&eacute;tiers de la m&eacute;diation sociale.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The mediation is a mode of resolution of conflicts in full rise, which proposes at the society a rehandling its ways of thinking, to say and to act, inherited the years of economic and social crisis (1980/90). Settling little by little in a rather vast social field (school, family...), mediation in general and particularly that known as &amp;quot;social&amp;quot;, which in France, had recently profited during several years from measurement &amp;quot;young employment&amp;quot;, suffers from a lack of reference mark in its step of professionalism. By describing the limits and weaknesses of the process of professionalization, this article try to demonstrate the benefit of having to rely on a repository of skills that will help dispel the uncertainty around trades of social mediation.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(10959, 'Mythe d’une santé parfaite et attitudes face au miracle médical', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;L&rsquo;id&eacute;e quasi unanime qui s&rsquo;est d&eacute;gag&eacute;e de cette &eacute;tude, va dans le sens de l&rsquo;exclusion d&rsquo;une vie en parfaite sant&eacute;, et met en avant plut&ocirc;t le caract&egrave;re in&eacute;vitable de la maladie. Derri&egrave;re ce scepticisme ou ce r&eacute;alisme, se cache une grande diversit&eacute; quant &agrave; la nature des repr&eacute;sentations de la sant&eacute;, de la maladie, de la m&eacute;decine et de la soci&eacute;t&eacute;. Tant&ocirc;t la maladie est envisag&eacute;e comme une agression sociale, et l&rsquo;accent est mis alors sur le caract&egrave;re agressif, stressant et malsain de la soci&eacute;t&eacute; d&rsquo;aujourd&rsquo;hui. Dans ce cas, l&rsquo;action de la m&eacute;decine est approuv&eacute;e et m&ecirc;me sollicit&eacute;e. Tant&ocirc;t, elle est repr&eacute;sent&eacute;e comme un fait normal et naturel qui refl&egrave;te le contraste et la dynamique de la vie, ainsi que la dimension culturelle locale. L&rsquo;action m&eacute;dicale dans le but de restaurer une vie en parfaite sant&eacute;, est per&ccedil;ue dans ce contexte comme une pr&eacute;tention, une intrusion voire une transgression de l&rsquo;ordre naturel et sacr&eacute;. L&rsquo;autre id&eacute;e cl&eacute;, est que les repr&eacute;sentations de l&rsquo;avenir de la sant&eacute;, outre le sentiment d&rsquo;inqui&eacute;tude et de pessimisme quant au sort des jeunes g&eacute;n&eacute;rations, montrent le rapport conflictuel du tunisien avec la soci&eacute;t&eacute; d&rsquo;aujourd&rsquo;hui. Comme elles refl&egrave;tent sa relation ambigu&euml; et probl&eacute;matique avec la m&eacute;decine moderne. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The most unanimous idea that has been deduced from this study goes towards the exclusion of life with perfect health and insists instead on the inevitable character of the disease. Behind that scepticism or realism hides a great diversity concerning the nature of the representations of the health, the sickness, the medicine and the society. In some certain cases, the disease is considered as a social aggression therefore, the focus is put on the aggressive, stressing and unhealthy character of the actual society. Thus the medical action is approved of and even appreciated. In other cases, the disease is represented as a natural and normal fact that reflects the contrast and local cultural dimension. Hence, the medical action to restore a perfectly healthy life is perceived in this context as a pretension, an intrusion and even a transgression. The other key word is that the apart from the feeling of anxiety and pessimism regarding the fate of the young generations show the conflictual relationship of the Tunisian with the modern society as it reflects his ambiguous and problematic relationship with the modern medicine.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;Analyse des représentations de la santé, de la maladie et de la médecine dans un pays arabo-islamique. (Le cas tunisien)'),
(10960, 'El desplazado en la guerra: representación y exclusión en nuestra América,  Montería (2005-2007)', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;es&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumen&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;El desplazado ha constituido un hecho singular en el devenir hist&oacute;rico de nuestra Am&eacute;rica desde la conformaci&oacute;n de esta regi&oacute;n. Actualmente, en ella, los estragos de la guerra aumentan las cifras de desplazados. Especialmente en Colombia, la exclusi&oacute;n social del desplazado est&aacute; presente bajo la forma de lucha ante los intereses de clase que tratan de mantener las condiciones de exclusi&oacute;n entre el opresor y el oprimido. Este trabajo indaga la forma en que se integran las representaciones sociales del desplazado en las pr&aacute;cticas de exclusi&oacute;n ejercidas por la poblaci&oacute;n receptora hacia este actor, en Monter&iacute;a (2005-2007). Para alcanzar este objetivo se opt&oacute; por la interdisciplina como metodolog&iacute;a, con los aportes de la teor&iacute;a social y la representaci&oacute;n social. Concluimos que las representaciones sociales del desplazado despojado de su humanidad, funcionan como marco de referencia para interpretar la realidad &nbsp;y orientan las pr&aacute;cticas de exclusi&oacute;n del desplazado del seno de la sociedad.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The displaced has constituted a singular issue of the historical process of our America from its beginning in the region. Nowadays, in it, the havocs of the war increase the numbers of the displaced. Especially in Colombia, where the social exclusion of the displaced is present under the form of the class interests that try to maintain the conditions of exclusion between the oppressor and the oppressed. This work investigates the way how the social representations of the displaced are integrated in the practices of exclusion exercised by the resident population toward this actor, in Monteria, Colombia (2005-2007). To achieve this objective we have chosen the interdisciplinary methodology, emphasizing the contributions of the social theory and the social representation. After showing that, the social representations of the displaced, dispossessed of their humanity, operat like reference mark to interpret the reality, these orientate the exclusion practices and they are shaped by the ideology. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(10961, '¿ La Ratería?', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;es&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumen&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Se conoce como pirater&iacute;a el uso de materiales protegidos por el derecho de autor sin la autorizaci&oacute;n de su creador. El presente art&iacute;culo analiza los resultados de una investigaci&oacute;n realizada sobre h&aacute;bitos de consumo y motivaci&oacute;n para el uso de productos llamados &ldquo;pirata&rdquo; en estudiantes universitarios de la Ciudad de M&eacute;xico. Se encontr&oacute; que los universitarios presentan conciencia del da&ntilde;o econ&oacute;mico y la problem&aacute;tica social que representa la pirater&iacute;a en M&eacute;xico sin embargo consumen productos pirata con frecuencia motivados principalmente por un &iacute;mpetu de rebeld&iacute;a contra las instituciones y empresas transnacionales.El consumo de pirater&iacute;a en Universitarios se ve influido por factores sociales, familiares y acad&eacute;micos m&aacute;s que econ&oacute;micos. Los factores psicol&oacute;gicos como la motivaci&oacute;n por rebeld&iacute;a, la influencia familiar y social se relacionan con aspectos propios de la cultura Mexicana. Los resultados se discuten a la luz de los postulados te&oacute;ricos de D&iacute;az-Guerrero, S. Freud y P. Ricoeur.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Piracy is defined as the illegal use or copy of copyright protected material without the authorization of its author. The present article analyzes the outcomes of a previous research done in Mexican Universities about the use and motivations around consume of pirate products. It was found that students are conscious of the social and economic damage piracy implies for Mexico, yet they frequently use pirate products motivated by a will to revolt against National Institutions and foreign transnational enterprises. Students consume of pirate products is directly influenced by social, familiar and academic factors more than economic ones. Some of the psychological factors found as a motivation for consuming pirate products are directly related to particular traits in Mexican culture. Results are discussed using authors such D&iacute;az-Guerrero, S. Freud and P. Ricoeur.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;Mitos y Realidades sobre un Fenómeno Socioeconómico en México*');
