(11020, 'Utilité et désirabilité d\'informations normatives sur des subordonnés et des collègues de travail', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Diverses &eacute;tudes ont &eacute;t&eacute; r&eacute;alis&eacute;es sur la valeur d&#039;autrui caract&eacute;ris&eacute; par des traits de personnalit&eacute; ou une profession. Nous avons ici choisi d&#039;&eacute;tudier non plus la valeur d&#039;&#039;une personne mais la valeur d&#039;informations portant sur cette personne. 426 salari&eacute;s, r&eacute;partis en 8 groupes ind&eacute;pendants, ont ainsi indiqu&eacute;, par 2 proc&eacute;dures diff&eacute;rentes, la d&eacute;sirabilit&eacute; et l&#039;utilit&eacute; qu&#039;ils attribuaient &agrave; des informations r&eacute;f&eacute;rant au degr&eacute; d&#039;adh&eacute;sions normatives d&#039;un futur subordonn&eacute; ou d&#039;un futur pair. Nous observons alors, outre des r&eacute;sultats divergeants selon la proc&eacute;dure, notamment de la part des responsables d&#039;encadrement, que la d&eacute;sirabilit&eacute; et l&#039;utilit&eacute; constituent deux dimensions de la valeur non syst&eacute;matiquement li&eacute;es. Nous constatons &eacute;galement que les jugements diff&egrave;rent selon le statut du futur collaborateur (subordonn&eacute; ou pair) et selon la norme sur laquelle porte l&#039;information (internalit&eacute;, croyance au monde juste, all&eacute;geance). &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11021, 'Réflexions : révolte et morale (Koestler et Camus)', 'titre_article', 6, ';'),
(11022, 'Political psychology in spain', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Political psychology is a relatively new, active discipline in Spain with historic lines of development. Using Ortega&#039;s concept of generation we trace the intellectual antecedents (1898-1936) and subsequent consolidation of the field. Scientific developments in psychology and political realities of the country comprise important influences in the development of the discipline. Identified empirically the main topics of political psychology in the period 1950-1990 are ideology, nationalism, political participation, and political culture. In the 1990s political psychology was closely tied to intellectual movements previous to the Spanish civil war. Nationalism, regionalism, and Spain&rsquo;s involvement in the tradition of Western democracies have significant places in the development of the discipline. As the discipline grew, several important research groups evolved; their research emphases and the factors that influenced them are identified and discussed.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
