(11153, 'Ethique et société dans l’œuvre de B.F. Skinner', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Pr&egrave;s de vingt ans apr&egrave;s sa mort, Skinner reste un des auteurs les plus controvers&eacute;s et les plus incompris tant dans le champ de la psychologie que dans le champ de la philosophie. Cet article reprend un certain nombre de concepts pol&eacute;miques et entend clarifier la position de Skinner par rapport &agrave; la double th&eacute;matique &laquo;&nbsp;&eacute;thique et soci&eacute;t&eacute;&nbsp;&raquo;. &lt;br /&gt;Partant d&rsquo;un r&eacute;examen du concept de personne, cet article se propose de r&eacute;examiner comment Skinner concevait le comportement humain comme objet d&rsquo;&eacute;tude en soi, au sein d&rsquo;une approche d&eacute;terministe et comment celle-ci le distinguait de l&rsquo;humanisme et constituait un approche incompatible avec l&rsquo;individualisme. &lt;br /&gt;La question du contr&ocirc;le du comportement est &eacute;galement abord&eacute;e, qui permet de revisiter les valeurs sociopolitiques exprim&eacute;es dans l&rsquo;&oelig;uvre de Skinner, en particulier dans Walden Two (1948), et le r&ocirc;le attribu&eacute; &agrave; l&rsquo;&eacute;ducation dans la r&eacute;alisation de ce projet. Skinner y d&eacute;non&ccedil;ait en particulier l&rsquo;usage du contr&ocirc;le de type aversif, autour duquel surgissent de nombreuses interrogations &eacute;thiques, et dont la permanence ne peut que nous questionner. Le projet de modification du comportement a ainsi &eacute;t&eacute; con&ccedil;u comme une proposition alternative au contr&ocirc;le aversif, s&rsquo;appuyant essentiellement sur le renforcement positif. &lt;br /&gt;De plus, un des probl&egrave;mes identifi&eacute;s par Skinner renvoie aux implications &eacute;thiques li&eacute;es &agrave; la perte de renfor&ccedil;ateurs naturels et sociaux r&eacute;sultant de l&rsquo;histoire des groupes humains et des conditions de vie, en particulier de l&rsquo;industrialisation. Una analyse minutieuse r&eacute;v&egrave;le que Skinner a toujours &eacute;t&eacute; un fervent critique de la soci&eacute;t&eacute; de consommation, analysant comment celle-ci a impos&eacute; des contingences de renforcement &eacute;troitement li&eacute;es &agrave; l&rsquo;application non-&eacute;thique de proc&eacute;dures de renforcement, que celui-ci soit naturel ou artificiel. &lt;br /&gt;Si Skinner n&rsquo;a jamais dout&eacute; de la n&eacute;cessit&eacute; d&rsquo;accepter la notion de contr&ocirc;le du comportement, sa pr&eacute;occupation majeure n&rsquo;a pas &eacute;t&eacute; de savoir qui contr&ocirc;le mais plut&ocirc;t qu&rsquo;est ce qui contr&ocirc;le, en d&rsquo;autres termes d&rsquo;identifier toutes les variables dont le comportement d&eacute;pend. Au fond, depuis 1948, son objectif a toujours &eacute;t&eacute; d&rsquo;aller vers un monde dans lequel chacun puisse profiter des sentiments de dignit&eacute; et de libert&eacute;. Selon lui, cela implique que nous devenions experts de ce qui contr&ocirc;le notre propre comportement afin d&rsquo;&eacute;viter le sentiment d&rsquo;&ecirc;tre manipul&eacute; par quelqu&rsquo;un. En ce sens, nier ou refuser le contr&ocirc;le ne constitue pas une solution et il s&rsquo;agit plut&ocirc;t d&rsquo;accepter l&rsquo;existence de ces variables de contr&ocirc;le, d&rsquo;y avoir acc&egrave;s au travers de leur connaissance et d&rsquo;organiser son comportement en fonction d&rsquo;elles. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Nearly twenty years after his death, Skinner remains one of the most controversial and misunderstood authors in the fields of psychology and philosophy. This article revises several of his polemical concepts and intends to clarify the position of Skinner with regard to the double theme &ldquo;ethics and society &amp;quot;.&lt;br /&gt;Starting with a review of the concept of person, this article intends to reconsider how Skinner conceived human behavior as an object of study in itself, in a deterministic approach, and how it differed from the humanistic and individualistic approaches. &lt;br /&gt;The issue of behavior control is also discussed, which allows us to revisit the socio-political values expressed in Skinner&#039;s work, especially in Walden Two (1948), and the role attributed to education in this project. Skinner criticized in particular the use of aversive control, around which many ethical questions arise, and whose permanence should question us. His behavior modification project has been designed as an alternative proposal to aversive control, mainly based on positive reinforcement. &lt;br /&gt;Furthermore, one of the problems identified by Skinner refers to the ethical implications of the loss of natural and social reinforcers resulting from the history of human groups and living conditions, especially industrialization. A careful analysis reveals that Skinner has always been a strong critic of the consumer society, analyzing how it has imposed reinforcement contingencies closely related to the implementation of unethical natural or artificial reinforcing procedures.&lt;br /&gt;Skinner&rsquo;s major concern was not who controls but rather what controls: in other words to identify all the variables on which behavior depend. Basically, since 1948, his goal has always been to move towards a world in which everyone can enjoy feelings of dignity and freedom. In his view, this means that we become experts of what controls our own behavior so as to avoid the feeling of being manipulated by someone else. In this perspective, deny or refuse the reality of behavior control is not a solution. We should rather accept the reality of these controlling variables so as to be able to know them and to organize our behavior according to them.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11154, 'Les conflits postélectoraux en Afrique subsaharienne', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Tr&egrave;s fr&eacute;quemment, lorsque les journalistes rendent compte d&rsquo;un conflit post&eacute;lectoral en Afrique subsaharienne, les explications qu&rsquo;ils proposent s&rsquo;appuient sur les diff&eacute;rences ethniques ou religieuses des populations impliqu&eacute;es dans ce conflit. Ce faisant, ils passent bien souvent sous silence les sources r&eacute;elles du conflit. &lt;br /&gt;Se basant sur les r&eacute;cents cas du Nigeria et de la C&ocirc;te d&rsquo;Ivoire, cet article poursuit deux buts. Tout d&rsquo;abord, il souhaite mettre en &eacute;vidence les &eacute;l&eacute;ments qui sont g&eacute;n&eacute;ralement &agrave; l&rsquo;origine des conflits post&eacute;lectoraux en Afrique subsaharienne. Dans un second temps, il vise &agrave; pr&eacute;senter certaines hypoth&egrave;ses qui peuvent expliquer pourquoi les journalistes privil&eacute;gient souvent une explication des conflits bas&eacute;e sur l&rsquo;identit&eacute; des protagonistes plut&ocirc;t qu&rsquo;une pr&eacute;sentation des enjeux qui sous-tendent les hostilit&eacute;s. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Postelectoral conflicts in subsaharian Africa&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;When journalists write or speak about a postelectoral conflict in subsaharian Africa, they frequently base their explanations on ethnical or religious differences between the populations implicated. Acting so, they often neglect to mention the reel sources of the conflict. &lt;br /&gt;Based on Nigerian and Ivory Coast recent conflicts, this article has two main objectives&nbsp;: first to expose the elements generally at the root of postelectoral conflicts in subsaharian Africa&nbsp;; second to present some of the hypothesis that could explain why journalists often give priority to explanations on the identity of the protagonists instead of issues at the root of the hostility. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11155, 'Un nouvel acteur politique ? Jeunes et action politique au Brésil', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Ce travail pr&eacute;sente une analyse des possibilit&eacute;s politiques de la jeunesse, en tant que cat&eacute;gorie sociale, au Br&eacute;sil. L&rsquo;argument vise &agrave; tracer des modes et positions de parole des jeunes produits au long du XXe si&egrave;cle, et &agrave; analyser les discours juv&eacute;niles sous la perspective de comment ils concourent &agrave; leur devenir politique. Nous comprenons que l&rsquo;&eacute;mergence d&rsquo;un &lt;em&gt;sujet politique&lt;/em&gt; a lieu dans la mesure o&ugrave; se signifient et se d&eacute;noncent des situations d&rsquo;oppression et injustice, v&eacute;cues par un groupe en particulier, mais qui, en m&ecirc;me temps, font tous voir des situations d&rsquo;injustice, agrandissant les sens de l&rsquo;&eacute;galit&eacute; et de la justice. La lutte pour l&rsquo;&eacute;ducation, telle que guid&eacute;e dans quelques mouvements r&eacute;cents de jeunes au Br&eacute;sil, semble permettre un &lsquo;moment politique&rsquo; pour la jeunesse, quoique les risques de cette demande puissent emp&ecirc;cher l&rsquo;encore naissante pr&eacute;sence politique des jeunes sur la sc&egrave;ne publique. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;es&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumen&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Este trabalho apresenta uma an&aacute;lise das possibilidades pol&iacute;ticas da juventude, como categoria social, no Brasil. O argumento visa rastrear modos e posi&ccedil;&otilde;es de fala dos jovens produzidos ao longo do s&eacute;culo XX, e analisar os discursos juvenis sob a perspectiva de como concorrem para seu devir pol&iacute;tico. Compreendemos que a emerg&ecirc;ncia de um &lt;em&gt;sujeito&lt;/em&gt; &lt;em&gt;pol&iacute;tico&lt;/em&gt; se d&aacute; na medida em que se significam e se denunciam situa&ccedil;&otilde;es de opress&atilde;o e injusti&ccedil;a, sofridas por um grupo em particular, mas que, ao mesmo tempo, fazem ver a todos situa&ccedil;&otilde;es de injusti&ccedil;a, ampliando os sentidos da igualdade e da justi&ccedil;a. A luta por educa&ccedil;&atilde;o, tal como pautada em alguns movimentos recentes de jovens no Brasil, parece viabilizar um &lsquo;momento pol&iacute;tico&rsquo; para a juventude, ainda que os riscos desta demanda possam inviabilizar a ainda incipiente presen&ccedil;a pol&iacute;tica dos jovens no cen&aacute;rio p&uacute;blico. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;This paper presents an analysis of the political possibilities of youth, as a social category, in Brazil. The argument delineates the modes and speech positions of young people along the 20th century, in order to analyse how the discourse practices produced by youngsters are conducive to their becoming political. It is understood that the emergence of a &lt;em&gt;political subject &lt;/em&gt;takes place insofar as situations of injustice and oppression, suffered by a particular group, are signified and denounced, while at the same time they are used to make explicit and known to all practices of injustice, which alters and amplifies present conceptions of equality and justice. The struggle for education, as it is found in the recent agenda of some youth movements in Brazil, seems to make possible a &lsquo;political moment&rsquo; for youth, even if the risks of these demands can outstrip their incipient political presence in the public scene.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
