(11162, 'La spécificité de la negotiation internationale', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;La pr&eacute;occupation actuelle, dans le nombre de conflits locaux ou internationaux, o&ugrave; se posent des probl&egrave;mes de r&eacute;conciliation, d&rsquo;identit&eacute; collectives, d&rsquo;interd&eacute;pendances politiques, s&eacute;curitaires, &eacute;conomiques et environnementales est en faveur d&rsquo;un regard plus attentif sur ces questions &ndash; ce qui ne peut, que favoriser de telles n&eacute;gociations internationales. La n&eacute;gociation internationale est une proc&eacute;dure de d&eacute;cision complexe et sp&eacute;cifique par laquelle les gens tendent de trouver un accord commun au lieu d&rsquo;agir par voie unilat&eacute;rale. Outil privil&eacute;gi&eacute; de l&rsquo;&eacute;change entre les hommes, de l&rsquo;ajustement de leurs points de vue, de coexistence de leurs identit&eacute;s sociales et de la r&eacute;solution de leurs conflits, la n&eacute;gociation internationale est l&rsquo;un des ressorts les plus fondamentaux de la vie. De plus, la n&eacute;gociation internationale de tous les types (diplomatique, politique, commerciale, culturelle, &eacute;conomique, environnementale) est affect&eacute;e par les ph&eacute;nom&egrave;nes culturels : aux divergences des buts et des objectifs, qui s&eacute;parent les n&eacute;gociateurs, s&rsquo;ajoute ici, une diff&eacute;rence culturelle, qui peut les rendre difficiles et opaques. La culture influence consid&eacute;rablement le processus, la communication, la cognition, la motivation et les actions des protagonistes. La connaissance des particularit&eacute;s &nbsp;culturelles de la partie adverse pourrait avoir un effet positif sur la perception du pays et sur la communication des n&eacute;gociateurs et la recherche des solutions, par contre, son ignorance ou n&eacute;gligence peuvent provoquer des complications, des risques de d&eacute;saccords ou d&rsquo;interruptions de n&eacute;gociation, etc. De plus, le n&eacute;gociateur international se trouve dans une position de l&rsquo;interface de deux relations, celle avec son propre pays et celle avec la partie adverse. Son dilemme, ici, pris en tenailles entre des objectifs contradictoires est de d&eacute;fendre les positions de son propre pays, ses propres int&eacute;r&ecirc;ts et parvenir &agrave; un accord avec la partie adverse. Dans notre article, la litt&eacute;rature sur la sp&eacute;cificit&eacute; de la n&eacute;gociation internationale &eacute;tait analys&eacute;e selon trois dimensions&nbsp;: &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration:underline;&quot;&gt;la premi&egrave;re&lt;/span&gt; refl&egrave;te au processus dynamique de la n&eacute;gociation identitaire, &agrave; la durabilit&eacute; des identit&eacute;s et la diffusion ces identit&eacute;s dans une population concr&egrave;te, &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration:underline;&quot;&gt;la deuxi&egrave;m&lt;/span&gt;e concerne l&rsquo;analyse des diff&eacute;rences culturelles et leurs impact sur le comportements des n&eacute;gociateurs (leur flexibilit&eacute; ou rigidit&eacute; dans le recherche des solutions) et, enfin , &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration:underline;&quot;&gt;la troisi&egrave;me &lt;/span&gt;concerne l&rsquo;analyse du r&ocirc;le de la personnalit&eacute; des n&eacute;gociateurs dans le d&eacute;roulement du processus d&rsquo;interaction et d&rsquo;interd&eacute;pendance (le r&ocirc;le jou&eacute; des politiques participant &agrave; la n&eacute;gociation, la cr&eacute;dibilit&eacute; des engagements et leur volont&eacute; d&rsquo;entrer dans les accords internationaux). &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The specificity of international negotiation&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;In an era of the change in international affairs, the are many significant examples of interdependence in the fields of politics, security, economics and environment, which contract strongly with the increasing number of conflicts caused by nationalistic or ethnic issues. These contradictory trends often seek resolution through the mechanism of international negotiation. International negotiation is a complex and specific process by which two or more protagonists of different nationalities interact with the aim of reaching an acceptable position given their differences. Just as the process of negotiating over divergent interests is influences by the parties&rsquo; identities, the identities are shaped by the way the process is conducted. However, culture profoundly influences negotiation process, communication, cognition, motivation and behave. More specifically, international negotiation of all types (political, diplomatic, economic, commercial, scientific, etc.) is always affected by cultural phenomena which can make relations difficult and non-transparent. Successful international negotiations require an understanding of the negotiation style of those on the other side of the table, and the acceptance and respect of their cultural beliefs and norm. On the other way, ignoring and negligent culture differences can create barriers that hinder agreements or complicate the unfurling of the negotiation process. That&rsquo;s why culture represents a major risk factor in international negotiation. Hey will have to be harmonized in order to establish the appropriate strategies, styles and tactics required to reach an easy solution. The negotiator&rsquo;s dilemma here, caught between contradictory objectives, is to defend the positions of his own field/group and his own interests and reach an agreement with the opposing party. Negotiating solutions to such problems is difficult for several reasons. Key among the challenges is the needs to negotiate the information base, which can itself be a source of contention that can stall the decision processor, bring it to court. Contributions from the literature on the specificity of international negotiation theory are discussed in terms of thee dimensions: &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration:underline;&quot;&gt;one dimension&lt;/span&gt; refers to a dynamic process of negotiating identities, the durability of identity and the spread of identities in a population,&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration:underline;&quot;&gt; another dimension&lt;/span&gt; refers to the cultural differences which are shown to have implications for the negotiating flexibility and rigidity of representatives and their constituents &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration:underline;&quot;&gt;and third dimension&lt;/span&gt; concerns the analysis of the role of the negotiators personality (adversary) in the development of processes of the interaction and the interdependence (the role played by national politics in international negotiation, the credibility of negotiating commitments and their willingness to enter into international agreements). &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
