(11243, 'Stress ou traumatisme ? Remarques sur quelques enjeux épistémologiques d\'une opposition conceptuelle et diagnostique', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;La pr&eacute;valence actuelle du stress sur le traumatisme dans l&#039;&eacute;valuation des souffrances au travail rel&egrave;ve d&#039;un rapport de forces favorable &agrave; la construction d&#039;une repr&eacute;sentation de la &laquo;&nbsp;souffrance au travail&nbsp;&raquo; conforme aux attentes sociales actuelles pour lesquelles la figure de l&#039;employ&eacute; stress&eacute; pr&eacute;sente un visage plus acceptable que celui du traumatis&eacute; du travail. Nous posons en ce sens l&#039;hypoth&egrave;se d&#039;une absence d&eacute;n&eacute;gatrice de la probl&eacute;matique traumatique dans le champ des pathologies du travail alors que les relev&eacute;s empiriques en attestent largement les manifestations. Pour cela nous confrontons l&#039;horizon &eacute;pist&eacute;mologique de la stressologie au d&eacute;veloppement des pratiques sociales du travail associ&eacute;es &agrave; la &laquo;&nbsp;guerre &eacute;conomique&nbsp;&raquo;. Nous constatons qu&#039;un certain usage du &laquo;&nbsp;stress chronique&nbsp;&raquo; permet d&#039;euph&eacute;miser, sinon d&#039;occulter la dimension traumatique de certaines situations de travail par la r&eacute;f&eacute;rence &agrave; des mod&egrave;les th&eacute;oriques diluant les repr&eacute;sentations de la violence sociale. L&#039;invocation des formes de causalit&eacute; physiologique, m&eacute;canique ou probabiliste semblent en effet permettre d&#039;&eacute;vacuer globalement la question du sens des &eacute;v&eacute;nements, tout en mesurant efficacement la symptomatologie organique.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The present dominance of stress concerning traumatism in the evaluation of work suffering is dependent on a favourable forces connection to the structure of the &laquo;&nbsp;suffering at work&nbsp;&raquo; perception which are in accordance to present social expectations for which the impression of the stress employee shows a more acceptable face than those of the work traumatised. In this meaning, we suppose the assumption of a deteriorate absence of the traumatically problematic in the work pathological scope even though the clinic highly certify the demonstrations. For that, we compare the survey of the epistemological of stressology with growth of social applications of work which are combined with &ldquo;economical war&rdquo;. We can see that some use of &ldquo;chronicle stress&rdquo; allows to euphemise, otherwise to occult the traumatically dimension of some situations of work by reference to theorist models which weaken the traumatically dimension of the social violence by the invocation of physiological, mechanical or probabilist causality lines which render possible to globally discharge the question of events sense while measuring organically answer with efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11244, 'Spartacus, héros de l\'antiquité et des temps modernes', 'titre_article', 6, ';'),
(11245, 'Il n’existe pas d’humanité universelle', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;La psychologie sociale traditionnelle a toujours rejet&eacute; les cat&eacute;gories entre personnes au nom de l&rsquo;&eacute;galit&eacute; et de l&rsquo;individualisme. Bien que les recherches r&eacute;centes montrent l&rsquo;efficacit&eacute; de la color-consciousness sur la color-blindness, cette derni&egrave;re est sp&eacute;cialement ancr&eacute;e dans les habitudes des citoyens des U.S.A. et se traduit notamment par le langage politiquement correct. Color-consciousness et color-blindness comportent chacune deux volets dont l&rsquo;un est raciste et l&rsquo;autre pas (ou moins). Alors que seul l&rsquo;individualisme d&eacute;fend l&rsquo;id&eacute;e d&rsquo;une humanit&eacute; universelle, je propose que la color-blindness, quel que soit son volet, comprend un monde r&eacute;duit au seul groupe d&rsquo;appartenance. Cette r&eacute;duction est compatible avec l&rsquo;id&eacute;e que son groupe est plus humain que certains autres groupes. Cette infrahumanisation justifie des actes immoraux de la part de son groupe, actuel ou pass&eacute;. Elle &eacute;vite &eacute;galement des affects d&eacute;sagr&eacute;ables comme la culpabilit&eacute; collective et la honte. Outre le volet de racisme explicite de la color-consciousness, la color-blindness remplit les conditions pour susciter de fr&eacute;quentes occurrences d&rsquo;infrahumanisation. Cette hypoth&egrave;se est paradoxale par rapport aux buts conscients de la color-blindness. Sans surprise, l&rsquo;int&eacute;gration ou le multiculturalisme qui admettent de nombreuses cat&eacute;gories devraient &ecirc;tre les moins sujettes &agrave; l&rsquo;infrahumanisation, aussi bien comme acteurs que comme victimes. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;For the sake of equality and individualism, social psychology has traditionally been reluctant to categorize people into groups. Although recent research has shown the efficiency of color-consciousness over color-blindness, US citizens remain faithful to color-blindness, notably when they practice politically correct language. Both color-blindness and color-consciousness comprise two sides, one being racist and the other not (or less). Individualism favors a universal humanity, but the author proposes that color-blindness in general considers the existence of a single group, the ingroup. This characteristic is compatible with the view that the ingroup is more human than outgroups. Infrahumanisation justifies past and present immoral acts committed by the ingroup. It also prevents from negative affects such as collective guilt and shame. Besides the racist aspect of color-consciousness, color-blindness offers frequent opportunities for infrahumanization. Such a hypothesis is a paradox with the conscious aims of color-blindness. Unsurprisingly, integration or multiculturalism, which allows many categories of people should infrahumanize and be infrahumanized least often. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11246, 'Unsilencing victims: the role of cross-cultural psychosocial interventions in reparation processes for victims of human rights violationsThe Inter-American System Experience', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Reparations for victims and survivors of severe human rights violations are a challenging field. It is during this process that victims often place their hopes of finding justice and redress. However, victims&rsquo; voices are frequently unheard and secondary victimization during proceedings is recurrent. In general, legal and social institutions are limited to a repair the irreparable. &lt;br /&gt;In Latin-America, but in many other places, this complexity has been even more intricate when the ethnic component is part of the scenario. &nbsp;Cultural differences are usually unidentified or overlooked.&lt;br /&gt;Psychosocial interventions and mental health care in cross-cultural reparation processes for human rights violations may contribute to redress victims and communities comprehensively. &nbsp;However, they face a number of epistemological and practical shortcomings (e.g. lack of interdisciplinary policies) that will be explored along the document. For this purpose, paradigmatic indigenous cases from the Inter-American Court of Human Rights are examined.&lt;br /&gt;Finally, I will argue that a more interdisciplinary research and practice combining law with social psychology and anthropology can innovatively advise policy makers&nbsp;in the global human rights area. &nbsp;Effective and adequate cross-cultural psychosocial processes, although they cannot ensure successful trial outcomes for victims, may still contribute to the victims&rsquo; recovery by promoting self-agency and sensitiveness.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11247, '¿Chavismo sin Chávez, es eso posible?', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Para poder avizorar que le depara a Venezuela el futuro, y en particular, al movimiento pol&iacute;tico que fund&oacute; Hugo Ch&aacute;vez y que lleva su nombre, &ldquo;chavismo&rdquo;, es necesario entender c&oacute;mo lleg&oacute; al poder este hombre y c&oacute;mo hizo para dominar el escenario pol&iacute;tico venezolano y hasta internacional desde 1999 hasta el 5 de marzo de 2013, fecha de su deceso. Para quienes lo admiraban en vida y lo siguen haciendo, y para aquellos que lo detestaban en vida y lo siguen haciendo, Hugo Ch&aacute;vez fue un gigante de la pol&iacute;tica que marc&oacute; con una huella indeleble m&aacute;s de una d&eacute;cada de la historia contempor&aacute;nea de Venezuela. Hugo Ch&aacute;vez fue m&aacute;s all&aacute; de ser un simple presidente de un pa&iacute;s subdesarrollado de la Am&eacute;rica del Sur, se transform&oacute; en un mito, en una figura m&iacute;stico religiosa que se puede observar hoy en d&iacute;a en cientos de altares a lo largo y ancho de Venezuela, donde adem&aacute;s de las figuras tradicionales de los santos a los que se les prenden velas y se les suplica ayuda, se puede observar el busto de Ch&aacute;vez vestido de militar y con su boina roja de paracaidista.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11248, 'A produção acadêmica sobre ações coletivas, participação política e movimentos sociais realizada nos Programas de Pós-Graduação em Psicologia no Brasil  (1987-2008)', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;es&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumen&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;O presente trabalho teve como objetivo investigar o cen&aacute;rio das publica&ccedil;&otilde;es cient&iacute;ficas relacionadas &agrave;s tem&aacute;ticas das pr&aacute;ticas pol&iacute;ticas, em especial, a participa&ccedil;&atilde;o em a&ccedil;&otilde;es coletivas, movimentos sociais e outras formas de participa&ccedil;&atilde;o pol&iacute;tica. Sendo assim, optamos por realizar um rastreamento no Banco de Teses da CAPES utilizando os seguintes descritores: &amp;quot;a&ccedil;&otilde;es coletivas&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;participa&ccedil;&atilde;o pol&iacute;tica&amp;quot; e &amp;quot;movimentos sociais&amp;quot;, com o intuito de localizar as pesquisas realizadas nos Programas de P&oacute;s-Gradua&ccedil;&atilde;o em Psicologia. Encontramos um total de 92 estudos e, considerando que alguns deles se repetiram, analisamos um total de 83 estudos. As pesquisas foram analisadas conforme o n&iacute;vel do estudo (mestrado ou doutorado); Institui&ccedil;&atilde;o de Ensino em que foi realizada; ano que foi publicada; aspectos te&oacute;rico-metodol&oacute;gicos e, por fim, conforme os objetivos do estudo. Em s&iacute;ntese, at&eacute; o momento da coleta de dados, pudemos constatar que: houve um crescimento do interesse pela tem&aacute;tica no Brasil, em especial, em meados da primeira d&eacute;cada deste s&eacute;culo; o n&uacute;mero de estudos realizados no n&iacute;vel do mestrado &eacute; tr&ecirc;s vezes maior que o n&uacute;mero de pesquisas realizadas no n&iacute;vel do doutorado; todas as pesquisas utilizaram o m&eacute;todo qualitativo, recebendo destaque o uso de entrevista e observa&ccedil;&atilde;o participante enquanto t&eacute;cnicas de pesquisa; a Pontif&iacute;cia Universidade Cat&oacute;lica de S&atilde;o Paulo (PUC-SP) &eacute; a Institui&ccedil;&atilde;o de Ensino que possui o maior n&uacute;mero de pesquisas nesta &aacute;rea respons&aacute;vel por 35% dos estudos produzidos. Por fim, os objetivos/objeto de estudo foram categorizados em ordem decrescente pelas tem&aacute;ticas: &ldquo;Movimentos Sociais e outras formas de participa&ccedil;&atilde;o pol&iacute;tica&rdquo; (n=25); &ldquo;Movimento Sem Terra&rdquo; (n=11); &ldquo;Rela&ccedil;&otilde;es de G&ecirc;nero&rdquo; e &ldquo;Produ&ccedil;&atilde;o de Subjetividades, modos de vida e pr&aacute;ticas pol&iacute;ticas&rdquo; (n=10); &ldquo;Associa&ccedil;&atilde;o de Moradores e Movimentos Populares&rdquo; e &ldquo;Movimentos Sociais e Sa&uacute;de&rdquo; (n=7); &ldquo;Comportamento Pol&iacute;tico&rdquo; e &ldquo;Consci&ecirc;ncia Pol&iacute;tica&rdquo; (n= 6); &ldquo;Estudo Te&oacute;rico&rdquo; (n=1).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Le but de ce travail a &eacute;t&eacute; l&#039;investigation du cadre des publications scientifiques par rapport aux th&eacute;matiques des pratiques politiques, en particulier, celles-l&agrave; de la participation aux actions collectives, aux mouvements sociaux et d&#039;autres genres de participation politique. De cette fa&ccedil;on, nous avons opt&eacute; pour faire une recherche dans la Banque de Donn&eacute;es des Th&egrave;ses de CAPES, en utilisant les mots descriptifs suivants: &amp;quot;des actions collectives&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;de la participation politique&amp;quot; et &amp;quot; des mouvements sociaux&amp;quot;, avec le but de rencontrer les recherches faites dans les Programmes de Post-Graduation en Psychologie. Nous avons rencontr&eacute; 92 &eacute;tudes et, en consid&eacute;rant que quelques uns se sont r&eacute;p&eacute;t&eacute;s, nous avons fait l&#039;analyse de 83 &eacute;tudes. Les recherches ont &eacute;t&eacute; analys&eacute;es au niveau d&#039;&eacute;tude (de ma&icirc;tre ou de docteur); d&egrave;s l&#039; Institution d&#039;Enseignement o&ugrave; elles ont &eacute;t&eacute; faites; l&#039;ann&eacute;e de la publication; des aspects th&eacute;oriques-m&eacute;thodologiques et, &agrave; la fin, selon les objectifs de l&#039;&eacute;tude. Par synth&egrave;se, jusqu&#039;au moment de la r&eacute;colte de donn&eacute;es, nous avons enregistr&eacute; le d&eacute;veloppement de l&#039;int&eacute;r&ecirc;t sur cette th&eacute;matique au Br&eacute;sil, particuli&egrave;rement, &agrave; la moiti&eacute; de la premi&egrave;re d&eacute;cade de notre si&egrave;cle; la quantit&eacute; d&#039;&eacute;tudes accomplis au niveau de ma&icirc;tre &eacute;tait trois fois plus grande que les recherches accomplies au niveau de doctorat; toutes les recherches ont employ&eacute; la m&eacute;thode qualitative, en mettant en &eacute;vidence l&#039; entretien et l&#039;observation participative comme des outils de recherche; la Pontif&iacute;cia Universidade Cat&oacute;lica de S&atilde;o Paulo (PUC-SP) est l&#039;Institution d&#039;Enseignement qui a le plus grand ensemble de recherches dans cet ordre d&#039;&eacute;tudes, en enregistrant 35% des &eacute;tudes produits.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The present study aimed to investigate the scenario of scientific publications related to the themes of political practices, in particular, participation in collective action, social movements and other forms of political participation. Therefore, we chose to perform a crawl in CAPES Theses using the following keywords: &amp;quot;collective actions&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;political participation&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;social movements&amp;quot;, in order to find the research conducted in the graduate programs in psychology. We found a total of 92 studies and, considering that some of them have been repeated, we reviewed a total of 83 studies. The surveys were analyzed according to the level of study (master&#039;s or doctorate); Educational institution in which it was held; year that was published; theoretical and methodological aspects and, finally, as the objectives of the study. In short, by the time of the data collection, we were able to see that: there was a growth of interest in the subject in Brazil, in particular, in the middle of the first decade of this century; the number of master &#039;s-level studies is three times greater than the number of searches carried out at the level of doctorate; all research used the qualitative method, getting the use of interviews and participant observation while research techniques; the Pontif&iacute;cia Universidade Cat&oacute;lica de S&atilde;o Paulo (PUC-SP) is the educational institution that has the greatest number of searches in this area accounts for 35% of the studies produced. Finally, the goals/object of study were categorized in descending order by themes: &amp;quot;social movements and other forms of political participation&amp;quot; (n = 25); &amp;quot;landless movements&amp;quot; (n = 11); &amp;quot;Gender relations&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;subjectivity Production, lifestyles and political practices&amp;quot; (n = 10); &amp;quot;Residents &#039; Association and popular movements&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;health and social movements&amp;quot; (n = 7); &amp;quot;Political Behavior&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;political awareness&amp;quot; (n = 6); &amp;quot;Theoretical study (n = 1).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11249, 'A Psicologia Política como campo interdisciplinar a partir da experiência da Escola de Artes, Ciências e Humanidades da Universidade de São Paulo', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;es&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumen&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;A cria&ccedil;&atilde;o do Grupo de Estudos e Pesquisa em Psicologia Pol&iacute;tica, Pol&iacute;ticas P&uacute;blicas e Multiculturalismo (GEPSIPOLIM) em 2007 foi o resultado de um esfor&ccedil;o interinstitucional, pois nasceu com a participa&ccedil;&atilde;o de pesquisadores da Universidade de S&atilde;o Paulo (USP), Universidade Estadual Paulista &ldquo;J&uacute;lio de Mesquita Filho&rdquo; (Unesp) e da Pontif&iacute;cia Universidade Cat&oacute;lica de S&atilde;o Paulo (PUC-SP). O novo grupo nasce marcadamente interdisciplinar, pois o comp&otilde;em pesquisadores que iniciaram suas trajet&oacute;rias na Filosofia, Pedagogia, Sociologia e Psicologia. O esfor&ccedil;o conjunto de alunos de gradua&ccedil;&atilde;o foi fundamental na consolida&ccedil;&atilde;o do grupo de pesquisa, uma vez que esses (as) pesquisadores-estudantes, por meio de suas investiga&ccedil;&otilde;es dirigidas por professores-doutores, ajudaram a tra&ccedil;ar de modo mais radical essa caracter&iacute;stica interdisciplinar, pois provinham de gradua&ccedil;&otilde;es de corte h&iacute;brido e encontraram na Psicologia Pol&iacute;tica um caminho seguro para responder muitas de suas inquietudes. Esses (as) estudantes trabalharam quest&otilde;es como g&ecirc;nero, direitos, movimentos sociais, pol&iacute;ticas p&uacute;blicas, rela&ccedil;&otilde;es multiculturais, sindicalismo, identidades coletivas, sempre fazendo pontes entre conhecimentos de fronteiras, preocupados (as) com os elementos subjetivos dos fen&ocirc;menos pol&iacute;ticos e coletivos. Diferentemente de outros grupos que concentram psic&oacute;logos, com p&oacute;s-gradua&ccedil;&atilde;o em Psicologia, este foi cada vez mais se abrindo para uma concep&ccedil;&atilde;o de Psicologia Pol&iacute;tica na qual a Psicologia e a Pol&iacute;tica sozinhas n&atilde;o s&atilde;o suficientes para responder as m&uacute;ltiplas quest&otilde;es que s&atilde;o pr&oacute;prias da Pol&iacute;tica e que n&atilde;o se reduzem a uma mera Psicologia da Pol&iacute;tica ou a uma Pol&iacute;tica da Psicologia. Assim, o GEPSIPOLIM vem se consolidando como um espa&ccedil;o plural e aberto aos encontros e &agrave; atua&ccedil;&atilde;o de pesquisadores (as) e estudantes da Escola de Artes, Ci&ecirc;ncias e Humanidades (uma unidade Interdisciplinar) da Universidade de S&atilde;o Paulo (EACH/USP). A partir do grupo da EACH/USP tamb&eacute;m nasceu o primeiro curso de especializa&ccedil;&atilde;o em Psicologia Pol&iacute;tica (Lato Sensu) do pa&iacute;s e contribuiu significativamente para a cria&ccedil;&atilde;o do Mestrado em Mudan&ccedil;a Social e Participa&ccedil;&atilde;o Pol&iacute;tica, no qual s&atilde;o ministradas as disciplinas de Psicologia Pol&iacute;tica e Pol&iacute;ticas P&uacute;blicas e de Psicologia dos Movimentos Sociais. Neste artigo, buscaremos realizar um exerc&iacute;cio de mem&oacute;ria sobre a pr&oacute;pria exist&ecirc;ncia do grupo, sobre suas a&ccedil;&otilde;es e suas produ&ccedil;&otilde;es intelectuais que revelam esta caracter&iacute;stica de interdisciplinaridade da Psicologia Pol&iacute;tica.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;La psychologie politique comme un chantier interdisciplinaire &agrave; partir de l&acute;exp&eacute;rience de l&acute;&Eacute;cole des Arts, Sciences et Humanit&eacute;s, de l&acute;Universit&eacute; de S&atilde;o Paulo&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;La cr&eacute;ation du Groupe d&#039;&Eacute;tudes et de Recherche en Psychologie Politique, Politiques Publiques et Multiculturalisme (GEPSIPOLIM) en 2007 a &eacute;t&eacute; le r&eacute;sultat d&#039;un effort inter-institutionnel, puisque il est n&eacute; avec la participation effective de chercheurs de l&#039;Universit&eacute; de S&atilde;o Paulo (USP), de l&acute;Universit&eacute; &laquo; Julio de Mesquisa Filho &raquo; (UNESP) et de l&#039;Universit&eacute; Catholique de S&atilde;o Paulo (PUC-SP). Le nouveau groupe est n&eacute; nettement interdisciplinaire, car il comprend des chercheurs qui ont commenc&eacute; leur carri&egrave;re en philosophie, p&eacute;dagogie, sociologie et psychologie. Toutefois, il est n&eacute; comme un groupe de recherche dans lequel le travail et le nombre d&#039;&eacute;tudiants de la licence &eacute;tait essentiel afin qu&acute;il puisse &ecirc;tre consolid&eacute;. Ces chercheurs-&eacute;tudiants, &agrave; travers de leurs enqu&ecirc;tes men&eacute;es par les enseignants, ont permis de consolider plus radicalement cette caract&eacute;ristique interdisciplinaire, car ils sont venus de diff&eacute;rentes licences et ils ont trouv&eacute;, dans la Psychologie Politique, un chantier s&ucirc;r pour la poursuite de leurs travaux. Ils ont travaill&eacute; sur les enjeux de genre, des droits, des mouvements sociaux, des politiques publiques, des relations multiculturelles, de syndicalisme, des identit&eacute;s collectives, en faisant toujours des liaisons entre la connaissance des fronti&egrave;res, toujours pr&eacute;occup&eacute;s avec les &eacute;l&eacute;ments subjectifs des ph&eacute;nom&egrave;nes politiques et collectives. Contrairement &agrave; d&#039;autres groupes o&ugrave; se concentrent des psychologues avec des &eacute;tudes sup&eacute;rieures en psychologie, le GEPSIPOLIM a &eacute;t&eacute; de plus en plus ouvert &agrave; une conception de la psychologie politique dans laquelle la psychologie et la politique elles-m&ecirc;mes ne suffisent pas &agrave; r&eacute;pondre aux nombreuses questions qui sont propres de la politique et qui ne se r&eacute;duisent pas &agrave; une psychologie de la politique ou une politique de la psychologie. Ainsi, ce groupe a &eacute;t&eacute; consolid&eacute; comme un espace pluriel et ouvert pour les d&eacute;bates et travaux des chercheurs et &eacute;tudiants de l&#039;&Eacute;cole des Arts, Sciences et Humanit&eacute;s, une facult&eacute; interdisciplinaire de l&acute;Universit&eacute; de Sao Paulo (USP). Du GEPSIPOLIM est &eacute;galement n&eacute; le premier Cours de Sp&eacute;cialisation en Psychologie Politique (lato sensu) du Br&eacute;sil, et il a contribu&eacute; de mani&egrave;re significative &agrave; la cr&eacute;ation du cours de Master en Changement Social et Participation Politique, dans lequel les disciplines &laquo; Psychologie Politique et les politiques publiques &raquo; et &laquo; Psychologie des mouvements sociaux &raquo; sont offertes. Dans cet article, nous effectuons un exercice de m&eacute;moire sur l&#039;existence m&ecirc;me du groupe au sujet de ses actions et sa production intellectuelle qui r&eacute;velent cette caract&eacute;ristique interdisciplinaire de la Psychologie Politique.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11250, 'Desafios para a ação participativa na gestão ambiental brasileira: uma análise psicopolítica', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;es&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumen&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Estudar os processos de participa&ccedil;&atilde;o relacionados &agrave; produ&ccedil;&atilde;o de uma pol&iacute;tica p&uacute;blica pode ser um elemento chave para a compreens&atilde;o do modelo de gest&atilde;o que se pretende implementar no Brasil, em especial em &aacute;reas de prote&ccedil;&atilde;o ambiental a partir das exig&ecirc;ncias brasileiras. A consolida&ccedil;&atilde;o de uma cultura democr&aacute;tica na gest&atilde;o de pol&iacute;ticas ambientais em unidades de conserva&ccedil;&atilde;o de uso sustent&aacute;vel passa pela compreens&atilde;o das din&acirc;micas comunit&aacute;rias e governamentais em processos de tomada de decis&atilde;o, como o da elabora&ccedil;&atilde;o de um plano de manejo. O presente artigo resulta de um trabalho de pesquisa que se prop&ocirc;s a compreender como se d&atilde;o tais processos de constru&ccedil;&atilde;o coletiva de um instrumento de gest&atilde;o p&uacute;blica e consolida&ccedil;&atilde;o de uma cultura pol&iacute;tica participativa a partir da produ&ccedil;&atilde;o do Plano de Manejo (PM) da &Aacute;rea de Prote&ccedil;&atilde;o Ambiental (APA) V&aacute;rzea do Rio Tiet&ecirc;, territ&oacute;rio que abrange 12 munic&iacute;pios da regi&atilde;o metropolitana de S&atilde;o Paulo (SP). Para atender este prop&oacute;sito foi utilizada a metodologia da observa&ccedil;&atilde;o participante para a coleta de dados em atividades p&uacute;blicas realizadas pela equipe gestora do PM da APA V&aacute;rzea do Rio Tiet&ecirc;, bem como a realiza&ccedil;&atilde;o de entrevistas semi-estruturadas com atores envolvidos na elabora&ccedil;&atilde;o do referido documento. A an&aacute;lise dos dados se deu a partir de base te&oacute;rica centrada nas discuss&otilde;es sobre consci&ecirc;ncia e participa&ccedil;&atilde;o pol&iacute;ticas, em um enfoque psicopol&iacute;tico, e nas discuss&otilde;es acerca da gest&atilde;o participativa de pol&iacute;ticas ambientais no Brasil. A pesquisa identificou que apesar da exist&ecirc;ncia de espa&ccedil;os formais de participa&ccedil;&atilde;o e tomada de decis&atilde;o de atores governamentais e n&atilde;o governamentais no processo de produ&ccedil;&atilde;o do PM da APA V&aacute;rzea do Rio Tiet&ecirc; - conforme exigido pela legisla&ccedil;&atilde;o vigente &nbsp;-, as estrat&eacute;gias adotadas por alguns participantes, bem como a no&ccedil;&atilde;o de participa&ccedil;&atilde;o e gest&atilde;o colegiada por eles destacadas - entre outros elementos -, apontam para desafios a serem superados para se assegurar a efetiva democratiza&ccedil;&atilde;o das decis&otilde;es e consolida&ccedil;&atilde;o de uma cultura pol&iacute;tica participativa na gest&atilde;o das pol&iacute;ticas ambientais. O presente trabalho destacou tamb&eacute;m as contribui&ccedil;&otilde;es da Psicologia Pol&iacute;tica para a an&aacute;lise e compreens&atilde;o de processos participativos democr&aacute;ticos.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11251, 'El miedo: fundamentos, rechazo y atraccion psicologica', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;es&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumen&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;A partir de revisar episodios hist&oacute;ricos, universales como privados hechos p&uacute;blicos, se repasan los elementos fisiol&oacute;gicos, psicol&oacute;gicos, sociol&oacute;gicos -psicosociales- e ideol&oacute;gicos que est&aacute;n en la base del miedo, o tambi&eacute;n terror, para hacerlo compatible con los episodios que sacuden al mundo. Asimismo, se repasa la doble condici&oacute;n de atracci&oacute;n y rechazo que ejerce el miedo sobre los humanos, desde la literatura, la cinematograf&iacute;a y la pl&aacute;stica.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Fear: foundations, psychological attraction and rejection&lt;br /&gt;The physiological, psychological, sociologial and ideological elements of fear are reviewed in the context of a study of historic episodes, both public and private. The article also considers, in the context of literature, cinema and plastic arts, both the attraction and rejection that fear exerts upon humans.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11252, 'Estrategias familiares de subsistencia: un caso de integración interdisciplinaria', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;es&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumen&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;El trabajo presenta el proceso que llev&oacute; a antrop&oacute;logos, soci&oacute;logos, dem&oacute;grafos y economistas de varios pa&iacute;ses de Am&eacute;rica latina a generar un campo integrado de investigaci&oacute;n en torno del estudio de las estrategias familiares de subsistencia, entre los a&ntilde;os setenta y los noventa del siglo XX. Primero se relata c&oacute;mo se configur&oacute; el inter&eacute;s sobre el tema en la sociolog&iacute;a urbana y en la antropolog&iacute;a rural, para despu&eacute;s examinar su confluencia en los estudios sobre crisis econ&oacute;micas, pobreza y respuestas de las familias, en el campo y en las ciudades. Se examinan las posiciones te&oacute;ricas y metodol&oacute;gicas en juego y se indica el campo de investigaci&oacute;n interdisciplinaria que se constituy&oacute;. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11253, 'El proyecto de una psicologia politica en el paraguay o el equilibrio entre historia, cultura y comportamiento', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;es&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumen&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;El estudio del comportamiento pol&iacute;tico como &aacute;rea especializada dentro de la psicolog&iacute;a ha comenzado a discutirse en el Paraguay fecha muy cercana. Pero pese a este comienzo reciente, existen antecedentes importantes que pueden encontrarse en la obra de historiadores, abogados y escritores de diversa procedencia que analizaron las peculiaridades del comportamiento de los paraguayos desde una perspectiva hist&oacute;rica y social. Esta aproximaci&oacute;n no constituye una elecci&oacute;n accidental ni arbitraria. La historia de este pa&iacute;s ofrece numerosas instancias desde donde puede enfocarse el proceso de construcci&oacute;n colectiva de la nacionalidad como una respuesta o alternativa al asedio sufrido por factores externos y a la acci&oacute;n de procesos pol&iacute;ticos y sociales internos. En el Paraguay se produjo un mestizaje muy activo durante la era colonial as&iacute; como una asimilaci&oacute;n de la cultura ind&iacute;gena al conjunto de costumbres y tradiciones que aportaron los colonizadores espa&ntilde;oles. A partir de all&iacute;, varios momentos importantes de la historia nacional pueden examinarse en busca de elementos y claves interpretativas para la configuraci&oacute;n del comportamiento pol&iacute;tico caracter&iacute;stico de los paraguayos. En s&iacute; mismos, estos factores que provienen de la historia y la cultura nacional no constituyen todav&iacute;a hip&oacute;tesis comprobadas susceptibles de integrar una teor&iacute;a del comportamiento pol&iacute;tico. Son insumos b&aacute;sicos con el potencial de contribuir a la identificaci&oacute;n de aqu&eacute;llos elementos que puedan ser objeto de una comprobaci&oacute;n posterior que a la vez utilice los recursos metodol&oacute;gicos de las actuales ciencias del comportamiento. Este cap&iacute;tulo ofrece una s&iacute;ntesis preliminar para configurar una agenda v&aacute;lida en la investigaci&oacute;n de la psicolog&iacute;a pol&iacute;tica en el Paraguay.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The study of political psychology as a specialized area within psychology began to be discussed in a very nearby date in Paraguay. But despite this recent inception, there are important precedents in the work of historians, lawyers and writers from diverse backgrounds who analyzed the peculiarities of the behavior of the Paraguayans from a historical and social perspective. This approach is not an accidental or arbitrary choice. The history of this country provides numerous instances where there can be studied the processes of collective construction of nationality as a response or alternative to the siege suffered by the influence of external factors and to the action of internal political and social processes. In Paraguay there was a very active miscegenation during the colonial era as well as an assimilation of the indigenous culture to the set of traditions and customs that provided the Spanish colonizers. From there, several important moments of the national history can be examined in search of elements and interpretative keys to understand the configuration of the political behavior typical of the Paraguayans. In themselves, these factors coming from the national history and culture are not yet proven hypothesis susceptible to integrate a theory of political behavior. They constitute basic inputs with the potential to contribute to the identification of those elements that may be subject to a subsequent check that simultaneously uses the current behavioral sciences methodological resources. This chapter offers a preliminary synthesis to configure a valid agenda for the research on political psychology in Paraguay.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
