(11255, 'Notas preliminares para una discusión acerca de las clases medias', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;es&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumen&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;El crecimiento de las clases medias y la disminuci&oacute;n de la pobreza pueden ser aprobadas por todos. Sin embargo, cu&aacute;nto es real, c&oacute;mo y por qu&eacute; hace aparecer diferencias te&oacute;ricas, emp&iacute;ricas e hist&oacute;ricas detr&aacute;s de las cuales aparecen supuestos y programas para el desarrollo de la sociedad actual.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The growth of middle classes and the reduction of poverty can be celebrated by everybody. However, how real are these measured changes? If they happen, why and how do they come to be? &nbsp;The answers to these questions show theoretical, empirical and historic differences hiding assumptions and blue-prints for the development of today society. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11256, 'Poor Youth and the Public School System: Challenges to Citizenship', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;This study reflects about an intervention-research based on the demands presented by the Municipal Public School of Belo Horizonte, Brazil. Grounded on the theoretical-methodological principles of Community Social Psychology, we analyzed the complex relation between youth, school and citizenship, with emphasis on the analysis of the dynamic of prejudices of gender, race, class, territory and sexuality. We called this analytical exercise the mapping of the wealth and difficulties of the school. We thus carried out participant observation in the school, semi-structured interviews with the directors and pedagogical coordinators, discussion groups with the students, teachers and familiars. The map afforded knowledge of the set of notions related to the conceptions of what it is to be a student, to be young in the suburbs, the role of the school, the role of the teachers in education, and what perspective of participating in the daily school life is possible for the various actors that are part of the school community.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;es&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumen&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;En este trabajo presentamos reflexiones acerca de una investigaci&oacute;n-intervenci&oacute;n basada en demandas presentadas por una Escuela Publica Municipal en Belo Horizonte, Brasil. A partir de los principios te&oacute;rico-metodol&oacute;gicos de la Psicolog&iacute;a Social Comunitaria, analizamos la compleja relaci&oacute;n entre juventud, escuela y ciudadan&iacute;a, con &eacute;nfasis en la din&aacute;mica de los prejuicios de g&eacute;nero, raza, clase, territorio y sexualidad. Llamamos este ejercicio anal&iacute;tico de mapa de las riquezas y dificultades de la escuela. Para eso, realizamos observaci&oacute;n-participante, entrevistas no-estructuradas con los directores y coordinadores pedag&oacute;gicos, grupos de discusi&oacute;n con estudiantes, profesores y familiares. &nbsp;El mapa de la escuela permiti&oacute; conocer y analizar el conjunto de concepciones acerca de lo que es ser alumno, joven en la periferia, el rol de la escuela y de los profesores y cual la perspectiva de participaci&oacute;n es posible para los diversos actores que integran la comunidad de la escuela. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11257, 'La psicologia politica en colombia', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The article presents a lecture of the production in the political psychology field in Colombia, where there are very few psychologists naming themselves as political psychologists. However, many of them have abundant production in the field but are named in other areas.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Based on the concept proposed by Maritza Montero, we collect and make visible the academic production that we consider enters in the political psychology field and we situate it in the lines of: political subjectivities, armed conflict, psycho-social support, memory, meanings of peace and gender. Trends in which we grouped the analyzed documents and collect much of the Colombian production in political psychology.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;es&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumen&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;El art&iacute;culo presenta una lectura de la producci&oacute;n en el campo de la psicolog&iacute;a pol&iacute;tica en Colombia, donde existen muy pocos psic&oacute;logos que se nombran a s&iacute; mismos como psic&oacute;logos pol&iacute;ticos. No obstante muchos de ellos tienen una producci&oacute;n abundante en el campo aunque se nominan en otras &aacute;reas.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumen&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;A partir de la concepci&oacute;n propuesta por Maritza Montero, recogemos y hacemos visible la producci&oacute;n acad&eacute;mica que consideramos entra en el campo de la psicolog&iacute;a pol&iacute;tica y la situamos en las l&iacute;neas: subjetividades pol&iacute;ticas, conflicto armado, acompa&ntilde;amiento psicosocial, memoria, significados de paz y g&eacute;nero. Vertientes en las que agrupamos la documentaci&oacute;n estudiada y que recogen buena parte de la producci&oacute;n colombiana en la psicolog&iacute;a pol&iacute;tica. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
