(11274, 'The Discourse of Body Politic in Thomas Hobbes’ Leviathan', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;This paper aims to analyze the occurrences of the metaphors of body politic and political disease in the treatise &lt;em&gt;Leviathan&lt;/em&gt;, written by one of the most influential political theorist from the seventeenth century, Thomas Hobbes. The concept of the state as a body politic, the analogy between the afflictions of the body and the &ldquo;afflictions&rdquo; of the state, the actions of the political actors seen as &ldquo;physicians&rdquo; of the said state had witnessed widespread use in early modern English political thought, in support of a wide range of political outlooks, from John Fortescue&rsquo;s &ldquo;constitutionalism&rdquo; to more absolutist templates proposed by the likes of Stephen Gardiner and Edward Forset. In the first half of the seventeenth century, serious changes occurred both in political philosophy and medicine, with respect to the traditional view of the body of man. These changes had in turn echoes in political thought, influencing both the language employed and the substance of the new political templates, and one such treatise where the mingling of the new and old body politic occurs is Thomas Hobbes&rsquo; &lt;em&gt;Leviathan&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11275, 'Analyse des répercussions d’une politique (post)coloniale sur les comportements actuels des Martiniquais', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;L&rsquo;histoire de la Martinique est li&eacute;e &agrave; la colonisation et &agrave; l&rsquo;esclavage pratiqu&eacute;s durant plusieurs si&egrave;cles par les Espagnols, les Anglais, les Fran&ccedil;ais et les Hollandais. Ces &eacute;v&eacute;nements qui ont cr&eacute;&eacute; un traumatisme psychique tant chez les esclaves et leurs descendants que chez les colons et leurs descendants, emp&ecirc;che l&rsquo;av&egrave;nement d&rsquo;un apaisement social, les souffrances qui en d&eacute;coulent n&rsquo;&eacute;tant pas trait&eacute;es. L&rsquo;objectif premier de cet article est d&rsquo;apporter un &eacute;clairage sur les r&eacute;percussions de cette &eacute;poque coloniale sur le comportement actuel du Martiniquais. Nous analysons la fa&ccedil;on dont le trauma s&rsquo;est fig&eacute; dans un complexe culturel transmis de g&eacute;n&eacute;ration en g&eacute;n&eacute;ration. Par ailleurs, si l&rsquo;&egrave;re coloniale est r&eacute;volue, son h&eacute;ritage continue d&rsquo;influencer le pr&eacute;sent notamment depuis le vote de la loi dite d&rsquo;&laquo;&nbsp;assimilation&nbsp;&raquo; de 1946. En effet, les d&eacute;cisions politiques post-coloniales n&rsquo;ont gu&egrave;re favoris&eacute; la construction identitaire du Martiniquais.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The history of Martinique is tightly related to colonisation and slavery applied for centuries by the Spanish, the English, the French and the Dutch. These events, which have created a psychic trauma as for the slaves and their descendants as among settlers and their descendants, hinders the emergence of a social pacification. The sufferings made have not been handled yet. The main goal of this article is to highlight the impact of the colonial period on the current behaviour of Martinique people. We analyse how the trauma was frozen in a cultural complex passed from generation to generation. Moreover, if the colonial era is gone, his inheritance still influences the present particularly since the passing of the so-called &amp;quot;assimilation&amp;quot; act in 1946. Indeed, postcolonial political decisions have hardly promoted the identity construction of the people from Martinique.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11276, 'L’influence des stéréotypes sur le déroulement de la négociation internationale commerciale', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;L&rsquo;objet de notre recherche est d&rsquo;&eacute;tudier l&rsquo;influence des st&eacute;r&eacute;otypes &agrave; l&rsquo;&eacute;gard de l&rsquo;exogroupe sur les rapports interd&eacute;pendants des sujets (fran&ccedil;ais et russes) durant la n&eacute;gociation internationale commerciale, ainsi que sur son r&eacute;sultat. L&rsquo;&eacute;tude exp&eacute;rimentale par le recours &agrave; la m&eacute;thode de la simulation analyse l&rsquo;effet de cette influence sur l&rsquo;&eacute;laboration des orientations strat&eacute;giques et les interventions des n&eacute;gociateurs. Les r&eacute;sultats obtenus r&eacute;v&egrave;lent un lien &eacute;tabli entre les st&eacute;r&eacute;otypes &agrave; l&rsquo;&eacute;gard de l&rsquo;exogroupe, le processus de la n&eacute;gociation, les comportements et les attitudes des sujets : les st&eacute;r&eacute;otypes n&eacute;gatifs renforcent une orientation strat&eacute;gique distributive, bas&eacute;e sur les interventions de comp&eacute;tition, la pression, les comportements rigides et les attitudes d&eacute;favorables ; les st&eacute;r&eacute;otypes positifs stimulent une orientation strat&eacute;gique int&eacute;grative, bas&eacute;e sur les interventions de la coop&eacute;ration, les &eacute;changes et les comportements flexibles, les attitudes d&eacute;favorables. Nous examinons &eacute;galement les principes de fonctionnement de processus de la prise de d&eacute;cision et les types des accords conclus (contenu, arguments employ&eacute;s, concessions effectu&eacute;es, &eacute;changes, etc.) qui d&eacute;terminent le partage des profits de deux sujets qui ont des st&eacute;r&eacute;otypes (n&eacute;gatifs ou positifs) &agrave; l&rsquo;&eacute;gard de l&rsquo;exogroupe. En conclusion, nos r&eacute;sultats obtenus confirment que l&rsquo;aboutissement d&rsquo;un accord mutuellement acceptable influence positivement le contenu des st&eacute;r&eacute;otypes &agrave; l&rsquo;&eacute;gard de l&rsquo;exogroupe.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;International negotiation is a complex and specific process by which two or more protagonists of different nationalities interact with the aim of reaching an acceptable position given their differences. The negotiator&rsquo;s dilemma here, caught between contradictory objectives, is to defend the positions of his own field/group and his own interests and reach an agreement with the opposing party. The aim of this research is to highlight the influence of the stereotypes in relation to the outgroup &ldquo;on the interdependency of interpersonal rapports of subject&rsquo;s (French and Russian) during international business negotiations and on the result. We have interpreted the effect of the influence on the choice of strategic direction with the major&rsquo;s axes the intervention&rsquo;s during the process of the negotiation simulation (method). Our results reveal a link between the stereotypes in relation to the out-group, the negotiation process and subjects&rsquo; behavior: negative stereotypes strengthen a distributive strategic orientation, reinforce interventions of competition and pressure, rigid behavior and unfavourable attitude; positive stereotypes encourage an integrative strategic orientation promote interventions of cooperation, logrolling, flexible behavior and favourable attitude. We examine the working of decision process and the types of the agreements (contents, utilized arguments, concessions, logrolling) determines the profits of the two subjects with stereotypes (negative, positive) with regard the out-group. Finally, the results are consistent with the hypothesis that we proposed as mutual acceptable agreement significantly influences the nature of the stereotypes in relation to the out-group.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11277, 'Silencios de la Psicología Política en Venezuela', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;es&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumen&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;El objetivo de este trabajo es describir el origen y desarrollo de la Psicolog&iacute;a Pol&iacute;tica en Venezuela en base a criterios estructurales (institucionalizaci&oacute;n del &aacute;rea) y acad&eacute;micos (los temas, teor&iacute;as y m&eacute;todos de investigaci&oacute;n) y evaluar su respuesta en relaci&oacute;n al acontecer nacional. Partiendo de la definici&oacute;n de Psicolog&iacute;a Pol&iacute;tica como la interacci&oacute;n entre los fen&oacute;menos pol&iacute;ticos y procesos y fen&oacute;menos psicol&oacute;gicos, se recopil&oacute; y organiz&oacute; la informaci&oacute;n acad&eacute;mica del pa&iacute;s desde los a&ntilde;os 60 cuando aparecen los primeros trabajos hasta el a&ntilde;o 2013. Para ello se utilizaron fuentes vivas (entrevistas con psic&oacute;logos activos) y revisi&oacute;n bibliogr&aacute;fica en las universidades donde se dictan cursos de pre y postgrado en psicolog&iacute;a, estas incluyeron publicaciones en revistas especializadas, textos, tesis de grado y postgrado y res&uacute;menes en eventos cient&iacute;ficos.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;pt&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumo&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Silenciando da Psicologia Pol&iacute;tica na Venezuela :&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;O objectivo deste artigo &eacute; descrever a origem e desenvolvimento da psicologia pol&iacute;tica na Venezuela com base em crit&eacute;rios estruturais (institucionaliza&ccedil;&atilde;o da &aacute;rea) e acad&eacute;micos (temas, teorias e m&eacute;todos de pesquisa) e avaliar a sua resposta em rela&ccedil;&atilde;o a eventos nacionais. A partir da defini&ccedil;&atilde;o de psicologia pol&iacute;tica como a interac&ccedil;&atilde;o entre os fen&oacute;menos e processos pol&iacute;ticos e fen&oacute;menos psicol&oacute;gicos, coligiu-se informa&ccedil;&atilde;o acad&eacute;mica do pa&iacute;s desde os anos 60, quando surgiram os primeiros trabalhos, at&eacute; 2013. Isto foi atingido utilizando fontes vivas (entrevistas com psic&oacute;logos no activo) e verifica&ccedil;&atilde;o bibliogr&aacute;fica das universidades onde se ministram cursos de licenciatura e p&oacute;s-gradua&ccedil;&atilde;o em psicologia, recorreram, ainda, a publica&ccedil;&otilde;es em revistas, textos, teses de p&oacute;s-gradua&ccedil;&atilde;o e resumos de apresenta&ccedil;&otilde;es em congressos cient&iacute;ficos.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Palavras chaves&lt;/strong&gt; : hist&oacute;ria, psicologia, pol&iacute;tica, Venezuela&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The aim of this paper is to describe the origin and development of political psychology in Venezuela based on structural (institutionalization of the area) and academic (topics, theories and research methods) criteria and evaluate their response in relation to national events. From the definition of political psychology as the interaction between the political and psychological processes and phenomena, the information was collected and organized with the aid of academic information from the 60, when the first works appeared, until 2013. This was accomplished by using real sources (interviews with psychologists) and bibliography that existed in the universities, where courses undergraduate and graduate courses in psychology were part of the curricula. It included publications in journals, texts, undergraduate and graduate thesis and abstracts presented in scientific meetings.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
