(11316, 'La racionalidad actual de los derechos humanos : lo jurídico, las ciencias humanas y la gubernamentalidad', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;La rationalit&eacute; actuelle des droits de l&#039;homme&nbsp;: droit, sciences humaines et gouvernementalit&eacute;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Le document suivant tente de r&eacute;fl&eacute;chir &agrave; comment les droits de l&#039;homme permettent d&#039;&eacute;tablir la relation entre savoir et pouvoir sur les deux l&#039;objectivation du m&acirc;le et de la subjectivation de la m&ecirc;me chose, mais en mettant l&#039;accent sur la relation des droits de l&#039;homme sur le r&ocirc;le du gouvernement&nbsp;: le comportement au volant de la population. Il est consid&eacute;r&eacute; comme une r&eacute;f&eacute;rence pour tenir compte de ce que Foucault d&eacute;velopp&eacute; par Miche cours de Coll&egrave;ge de France entre 1975 et 1978, et ses derni&egrave;res interventions politiques de 1982 et 1983 en mati&egrave;re de droits de la r&eacute;gie.&lt;br /&gt;Les droits humains sont un m&eacute;canisme qui est parce qu&#039;il int&egrave;gre universalistes de les aspects de la vie, le travail et la langue, et sont mercantiliste car ils re&ccedil;oivent les impacts d&#039;une v&eacute;rit&eacute; que le march&eacute;, avec sa logique de l&#039;accumulation et la production tout inocul&eacute; touches. Il est aussi juridique, car elle d&eacute;termine la condition des &ecirc;tres humains, alors que personne, communaut&eacute; ou minorit&eacute;, et que de nouveaux types et classifications &agrave; consid&eacute;rer. Les sciences humaines ont enrichi espaces, ont oxyg&eacute;n&eacute; les relations de pouvoir disciplinaire, l&#039;oppression, la surveillance, la m&eacute;dicalisation, l&#039;&eacute;ducation, l&#039;environnement, les politiques en g&eacute;n&eacute;ral. Droits de l&#039;homme, pour leur part, ont travaill&eacute; d&#039;une mani&egrave;re coercitive envers le savoir p&eacute;nitentiaire, m&eacute;dicale et juridique.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;es&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumen&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;El siguiente trabajo intenta reflexionar c&oacute;mo los Derechos Humanos permiten que se establezca la relaci&oacute;n entre saber y poder mediando tanto la objetivaci&oacute;n del hombre como la subjetivaci&oacute;n del mismo, pero acentuando la relaci&oacute;n de los Derechos Humanos sobre la funci&oacute;n del gobierno&nbsp;: la de conducir conductas de la poblaci&oacute;n. Se toma como eje para esta reflexi&oacute;n lo desarrollado por Miche Foucault en los cursos del College de France entre 1975 y 1978, y sus &uacute;ltimas intervenciones pol&iacute;ticas de 1982 y 1983 en relaci&oacute;n con derechos de los gobernados.&lt;br /&gt;Los derechos humanos son un mecanismo que es axiol&oacute;gico porque integra los aspectos universalistas de la vida, el trabajo y el lenguaje, y son mercantilistas porque reciben los impactos de una verdad que el mercado, que con su l&oacute;gica de acumulaci&oacute;n y producci&oacute;n inocula todo lo que toca. Es tambi&eacute;n jur&iacute;dico porque determina la condici&oacute;n de los seres humanos, en tanto que persona individual, colectividad o minor&iacute;a, y en tanto de nuevas tipolog&iacute;as y clasificaciones a considerar.&lt;br /&gt;Las ciencias del hombre han brindado aportes a los espacios, han oxigenado a las relaciones de poder disciplinarias, las de opresi&oacute;n, las de vigilancia, la de medicalizaci&oacute;n, las de educaci&oacute;n, las ecol&oacute;gicas, las pol&iacute;ticas en general. Los derechos humanos, por su parte, han funcionado en todos estos &aacute;mbitos coercitivamente hacia el mismo saber penitenciario, m&eacute;dico, y jur&iacute;dico.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11317, 'Reciprocidad, tipos de contingencias sociales sistémicas y lenguaje : investigación de las interacciones interindividuales', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;es&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumen&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Se examinan algunos supuestos te&oacute;ricos y metodol&oacute;gicos fundamentales para el an&aacute;lisis multidisciplinar de las interacciones interindividuales orientado por la l&oacute;gica general del paradigma interconductual y la propuesta particular de Ribes (2001) alrededor de las dimensiones funcionales de la conducta social.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Some fundamental theoretical and methodological assumptions for the multidisciplinary analysis of interindividual interactions oriented by the general logic of the interconductual paradigm and particular approach of Ribes (2001) about the functional dimensions of social behavior are examined.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11318, 'Psychological and Social well-being: the mediated role of values', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Several authors have studied the relationship between well-being and values, highlighting that it is partially determined by personal values that prevail in social environment (Basabe et al., 2002; Lima &amp;amp; Novo, 2006; Pa&eacute;z &amp;amp; Zubieta, 2004; Sagiv, Roccas &amp;amp; Hazan, 2004; Sagiv &amp;amp; Schwartz, 2000). Such studies are usually oriented to subjective well-being, while there is a lack of researches focused on psychological and social well-being dimensions. In order to analyze the mediated role of values in psychological and social well-being, a&nbsp;correlational&nbsp;study&nbsp;was carried out-&nbsp;non experimental transversal design. A convenience sample&nbsp;was used composed by 1062 participants&nbsp;(33.6% males-&nbsp;66.4% females, age&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&#039;Cambria Math&#039;,serif;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;M&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&#039;Cambria Math&#039;,serif;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;=26.73;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&#039;Cambria Math&#039;,serif;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;SD=10.01)from Argentina.&lt;br /&gt;Based on previous correlation analysis, eleven regressions (stepwise method) were carried out introducing values as psychological and social well-being dimensions predictors. Self-transcendence and openness to change values had significant betas in almost all psychological and social well-being dimensions while conservation values had a negative effect on positive relations with others, autonomy, personal growth, social acceptance and social coherence and self-promotion values on autonomy, environmental mastery, personal growth and social contribution.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11319, 'Sob o impacto destrutivo das violências na (des)construção das subjetividades: é possivel a resistências?', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;es&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resumen&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;O presente texto prop&otilde;e uma reflex&atilde;o a cerca das possibilidades de resist&ecirc;ncia humana frente &agrave;s injun&ccedil;&otilde;es excruciantes da cultura contempor&acirc;nea. Tendo como aporte te&oacute;rico a Psican&aacute;lise e a Teoria Cr&iacute;tica para articularmos indiv&iacute;duo e cultura, analisaremos como as condi&ccedil;&otilde;es de trabalho forjadas no capitalismo flex&iacute;vel levam os homens a tornarem-se cumplices da cultura que os avilta. Lan&ccedil;ados a condi&ccedil;&atilde;o de massa amorfa (Adorno, 1986), os homens s&atilde;o destitu&iacute;dos da sua capacidade de indigna&ccedil;&atilde;o frente &agrave;s injusti&ccedil;as sociais engendradas pelas condi&ccedil;&otilde;es de trabalho hostis a eles pr&oacute;prios. Por necessitarem de trabalho para garantirem sua sobreviv&ecirc;ncia n&atilde;o vislumbram outro caminho a n&atilde;o ser a ades&atilde;o &agrave;s inj&uacute;rias erigidas pelo modelo socioecon&ocirc;mico vigente. Entretanto, a mesma for&ccedil;a que o homem se serve para dar a ades&atilde;o a esse processo pode promover sua emancipa&ccedil;&atilde;o pelo estabelecimento de v&iacute;nculos solid&aacute;rios e historicizados entre os pares. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Current investigation instigates reflections on the possibility of human resistance in the wake of the excruciating laws of contemporary culture. Foregrounded on the theory of Psychoanalysis and Critical Theory to define the individual and culture, we will analyze how work conditions molded within flexible capitalism makes people become accomplices of the culture that degrades them. As Adorno (1986) remarks, they are spurned as an amorphous mass and stripped of their ability to be angry in the face of social injustice produced by the working conditions hostile to themselves. Since they need jobs to guarantee their physical survival, they fail to see any other pathway except adhering to the grievances inflicted by the dominant social and economical model. However, the same force that people use to provide adhesion to the process may promote their emancipation through the establishment of solidarity and historicized bonds among equals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;');
