(11320, 'Le rôle des stéréotypes nationaux dans les interactions interpersonnelles et intergroupales', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Cet article porte sur l&rsquo;analyse du r&ocirc;le des st&eacute;r&eacute;otypes nationaux dans les interactions interpersonnelles, intergroupales et la n&eacute;gociation dans le cadre de deux &eacute;tudes exp&eacute;rimentales. L&rsquo;objet de notre &eacute;tude exp&eacute;rimentale est d&rsquo;analyser les st&eacute;r&eacute;otypes des sujets de deux &eacute;chantillons &agrave; l&#039;&eacute;gard de l&#039;endogroupe et de l&rsquo;exogroupe et d&rsquo;&eacute;tablir leur lien avec la distance sociale et les valeurs. Les r&eacute;sultats obtenus montrent que les rapports entre &laquo;&nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration:underline;&quot;&gt;Nous&lt;/span&gt;&nbsp;&raquo; (l&#039;endogroupe) et &laquo;&nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration:underline;&quot;&gt;Eux&lt;/span&gt;&nbsp;&raquo; (l&#039;exogroupe) peuvent &ecirc;tre &eacute;tudi&eacute; de fa&ccedil;on suivante&nbsp;: a)&nbsp;le favoritisme de l&rsquo;exogroupe et l&rsquo;endogroupe, b)&nbsp;le d&eacute;favoritisme de l&#039;exogroupe et le favoritisme de l&rsquo;endogroupe, c)&nbsp;le favoritisme de l&#039;exogroupe et le d&eacute;favoritisme de l&rsquo;endogroupe, d)&nbsp;le d&eacute;favoritisme de l&rsquo;exogroupe et de l&rsquo;endogroupe. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;This article looks at an analysis of the role of national stereotypes in interpersonal/intergroup interactions in the experimental study. The objective of our experimental study is to analyse the stereotypes of subjects from two samples in relation to the in-group and the out-group and to establish a link with social distance and values. The results obtained show that the links between &ldquo;US&rdquo; (the in-group) and &ldquo;THEM&rdquo; (the out-group) can be studied as fallows: a)favouritism of the out-group and the in-group, b)defavouritism of the out-group and favouritism of the in-group, c)favouritism of the out-group and defavouritism of the in-group, d)defavouritism of the out-group and the in-group.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11321, 'Etude de la satisfaction du soutien psychosocial des personnes déeplacees internes à Abidjan', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;En C&ocirc;te d&rsquo;Ivoire, l&rsquo;&eacute;lection pr&eacute;sidentielle a d&eacute;bouch&eacute; sur une crise post&eacute;lectorale de 2010 &agrave; 2011. Cette crise a fait vivre aux populations des situations extr&ecirc;mes de stress, d&rsquo;angoisse et de terreur ayant entra&icirc;n&eacute; d&rsquo;importants d&eacute;placements de populations. Pendant et apr&egrave;s les hostilit&eacute;s, plusieurs personnes d&eacute;plac&eacute;es internes (PDI) ont re&ccedil;u un soutien psychosocial (SPS) destin&eacute; &agrave; les secourir et &agrave; les aider &agrave; faire face aux difficult&eacute;s rencontr&eacute;es. L&rsquo;objectif de l&rsquo;&eacute;tude pr&eacute;sent&eacute;e ici est d&rsquo;&eacute;valuer chez ces d&eacute;plac&eacute;es internes, la satisfaction du SPS re&ccedil;u dans une perspective d&rsquo;am&eacute;lioration des services offerts aux victimes d&rsquo;&eacute;v&eacute;nements dramatiques. A partir d&rsquo;une &eacute;chelle de satisfaction du soutien psychosocial distinguant les aspects sociaux des aspects psychologiques, et d&rsquo;un guide d&rsquo;entretien, 49 personnes d&eacute;plac&eacute;es internes ont &eacute;t&eacute; interrog&eacute;es &agrave; Yopougon, dans le district d&rsquo;Abidjan. Les r&eacute;sultats obtenus montrent que la grande majorit&eacute; des PDI a &eacute;t&eacute; satisfaite du SPS re&ccedil;u. Par ailleurs, le nombre de PDI satisfaites des aspects sociaux du soutien, est sup&eacute;rieur &agrave; celui qu&rsquo;on observe concernant les aspects psychologiques. Ces observations sugg&egrave;rent donc une formalisation et une professionnalisation de la prise en charge psychosociale des victimes des &eacute;v&eacute;nements dramatiques, une meilleure adaptation de la prise en charge psychosociale prenant en compte les diff&eacute;rences individuelles entre les victimes, la facilitation des processus de r&eacute;conciliation par la satisfaction du SPS re&ccedil;u.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;In Ivory Coast, the presidential election resulted in a post-election crisis of 2010-2011. This crisis has people living in situations of extreme stress, anxiety and terror that caused significant displacement. During and after the war, many internally displaced persons (IDPs) received psychosocial support for rescue and help them cope with difficulties. The aim of the present study is to evaluate in these IDPs, satisfaction SPS received with a view to improving services for victims of dramatic events. From a satisfaction scale psychosocial support distinguishing the social aspects of psychological aspects, and an interview guide, 49 IDPs were interviewed in Yopougon in Abidjan district. The results obtained show that the vast majority of DPIs has been satisfied received psychosocial support. Moreover, the number of IDPs met the social aspects of support is greater than that observed on the psychological aspects. These observations suggest a formalization and professionalization of psychosocial care for victims of the tragic events, a better adaptation of psychosocial care, taking into account individual differences between victims, facilitating reconciliation processes by satisfaction received psychosocial support.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11322, 'Causes et consequences de la catastrophe de Mpila au Congo-Brazzaville', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;De port&eacute;e nationale, transnationale et internationale, les catastrophes mini&egrave;res, ferroviaires, a&eacute;riennes, etc. tiennent une place importante dans l&#039;univers m&eacute;diatique, les conversations quotidiennes et les sciences. En psychologie sociale et politique, on peut s&#039;int&eacute;resser aux attributions causales et aux attributions de responsabilit&eacute; de catastrophe mobilis&eacute;es par les individus ou les groupes d&rsquo;individus. On entend par attribution le processus par lequel l&rsquo;homme cherche &agrave; organiser l&#039;environnement, &agrave; &eacute;laborer sa conception de la causalit&eacute; et/ou de la responsabilit&eacute; des &eacute;v&eacute;nements et des comportements. Il a le choix entre des attributions internes et des attributions externes qui maximisent ou minimisent la responsabilit&eacute; des individus ou des groupes d&rsquo;individus directement ou non impliqu&eacute;s dans le drame.&lt;br /&gt;L&rsquo;objectif de cette &eacute;tude &eacute;tait d&#039;identifier des causes et des responsables de la catastrophe de Mpila au Congo-Brazzaville. Penser catastrophe impliquait la d&eacute;signation de ses suppos&eacute;s responsables&nbsp;: le militaire, le politique, les dieux. Ainsi, des r&eacute;sultats &eacute;taient obtenus &agrave; partir de l&#039;analyse de contenu pratiqu&eacute;e sur des diff&eacute;rentes d&eacute;clarations des familles de victimes et des membres du parti politique au pouvoir. Ils montraient que des gouvern&eacute;s effectuaient des attributions internes d&eacute;favorables aux gouvernants (attributions accusatrices). En revanche, des gouvernants effectuaient des attributions externes favorables &agrave; eux-m&ecirc;mes (attributions d&eacute;fensives). &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Of national, transnational and international reach, the mining, railroad, air disasters and so forth hold an important place in the media universe, the daily conversations and the sciences. In social and political psychology, we can be interested in the individuals&rsquo;or groups&rsquo;causal and responsibility attributions of disasters. We mean by attribution the process by which the individual tries to organize the environment, to develop her or his conception of the causality and/or the responsibility for the occurrence of events and behaviors. The individual has choice between internal versus external attributions, which maximize or minimize the responsibility of the individuals or groups that are directly or not involved in those disasters. The objective of this study was to identify the causes of, and people responsible of the Mpila drama in Congo-Brazzaville. Thinking of the disaster implies identification of people that are supposedly responsible for it:the military, the politician, the gods. Content analyses were performed on various statements of victims&rsquo;families and members of the political party in power. The results show that citizens made internal and unfavorable attributions regarding the role of the government (accusatory attributions) in the occurrence of the disaster. In contrast, people in charge of the government made external attributions that were favorable to themeselves (defensive attributions).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
(11323, 'Sur l’homologie comme méthode d’approche de la psychologie politique', 'titre_article', 6, '&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;fr&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;resume&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Notre contribution reviendra sur ce pan de la s&eacute;miotique rossi-landienne qui concerne la proposition d&rsquo;une m&eacute;thode encore actuelle permettant d&rsquo;&eacute;tudier et de comprendre la soci&eacute;t&eacute;. L&rsquo;&lt;em&gt;homologie&lt;/em&gt; que Rossi-Landi &eacute;tablit entre la production mat&eacute;rielle et la production linguistique s&rsquo;av&egrave;re utile pour aborder des probl&egrave;mes scrut&eacute;s par la psychologie politique dans ses rapports &agrave; l&rsquo;&eacute;conomie, l&rsquo;id&eacute;ologie, l&rsquo;ali&eacute;nation, le travail, la domination, le langage et la praxis sociale.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;&lt;r2r:ml lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;abstract&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Our contribution will reconsider this side of the Rossi-Landian semiotics concerning the proposition of a method that is still up-to-date and allows us to study and understand society. The &lt;em&gt;homology&lt;/em&gt; that Rossi-Landi states between material production and linguistic production proves to be useful to approach problems observed by political psychology in its relationships with economics, ideology, alienation, work, domination, language and social praxis.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/r2r:ml&gt;;'),
